overview: >-
  The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetic appeal of
  their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic. The
  assistant began by conducting a thorough review of the app's existing visual
  components, including global CSS, layout, main pages, and UI elements. This
  analysis revealed a generic color palette, plain backgrounds, dense form
  sections, and an overall lack of visual personality suitable for a sleep
  health app.

  To address these issues, the assistant implemented a comprehensive aesthetic
  overhaul. Key changes included introducing a calming, sleep-themed color
  palette with deep indigos, purples, and teal accents, along with custom
  utility classes for gradients and shadows. The main questionnaire form
  received a redesigned progress indicator, decorative background blurs, and a
  subtle star pattern on the card header. The intro section was transformed with
  a hero element and feature cards, replacing simple bullet points. Core UI
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and the progress bar were
  polished with improved sizing, hover states, and gradient fills. Form field
  groupings were updated from basic gray boxes to more refined cards, and the
  report section was styled for a more professional final presentation. The
  changes aimed to create a more nuanced, trustworthy, and emotionally resonant
  interface.
